&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic and motivated Nurse to join our team on the Neuro Rehabilitation Centre at Goole.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a specialist rehabilitation service that provides acute and post-acute in-patient rehabilitation for adults with acquired brain injury and other neurological conditions. Located within the Goole and District Hospital, and managed by the Northern Lincolnshire and Goole NHS Foundation Trust (NLaG), the 14-bedded specialist centre accepts people at an earlier stage of recovery than is typical of most rehabilitation settings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have the opportunity to develop skills in caring for patients with Prolonged Disorders of Consciousness including those with tracheostomies.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Patients are supported by a Multidisciplinary Team, led by a Consultant in Rehabilitation Medicine. Other team members include Doctors, Registered Nurses, Occupational Therapists, Physiotherapist, Speech and Language Therapists, Psychologist and Dietetics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hannah Vaughan, Nurse Lead&lt;/p&gt;
